                <h2><a name="cite"></a>Share and Cite</h2>

                <div class="social-media-links" style="text-align: left;">
                    <a href="mailto:?&amp;subject=From%20MDPI%3A%20%22Face%20Boundary%20Formulation%20for%20Harmonic%20Models%3A%20Face%20Image%20Resembling&quot;&amp;body=https://www.mdpi.com/3124740%3A%0A%0AFace%20Boundary%20Formulation%20for%20Harmonic%20Models%3A%20Face%20Image%20Resembling%0A%0AAbstract%3A%20This%20paper%20is%20devoted%20to%20numerical%20algorithms%20based%20on%20harmonic%20transformations%20with%20two%20goals%3A%20%281%29%20face%20boundary%20formulation%20by%20blending%20techniques%20based%20on%20the%20known%20characteristic%20nodes%20and%20%282%29%20some%20challenging%20examples%20of%20face%20resembling.%20The%20formulation%20of%20the%20face%20boundary%20is%20imperative%20for%20face%20recognition%2C%20transformation%2C%20and%20combination.%20Mapping%20between%20the%20source%20and%20target%20face%20boundaries%20with%20constituent%20pixels%20is%20explored%20by%20two%20approaches%3A%20cubic%20spline%20interpolation%20and%20ordinary%20differential%20equation%20%28ODE%29%20using%20Hermite%20interpolation.%20The%20ODE%20approach%20is%20more%20flexible%20and%20suitable%20for%20handling%20different%20boundary%20conditions%2C%20such%20as%20the%20clamped%20and%20simple%20support%20conditions.%20The%20intrinsic%20relations%20between%20the%20cubic%20spline%20and%20ODE%20methods%20are%20explored%20for%20different%20face%20boundaries%2C%20and%20their%20combinations%20are%20developed.%20Face%20combination%20and%20resembling%20are%20performed%20by%20employing%20blending%20curves%20for%20generating%20the%20face%20boundary%2C%20and%20face%20images%20are%20converted%20by%20numerical%20methods%20for%20harmonic%20models%2C%20such%20as%20the%20finite%20difference%20method%20%28FDM%29%2C%20the%20finite%20element%20method%20%28FEM%29%20and%20the%20finite%20volume%20method%20%28FVM%29%20for%20harmonic%20models%2C%20and%20the%20splitting%26ndash%3Bintegrating%20method%20%28SIM%29%20for%20the%20resampling%20of%20constituent%20pixels.%20For%20the[...]" title="Email">
