            <div id="main-share-modal" class="reveal-modal reveal-modal-new reveal-modal-new--small" data-reveal aria-labelledby="modalTitle" aria-hidden="true" role="dialog">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="small-12 columns">
                <h2 style="margin: 0;">Share Link</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="small-12 columns">
                <div class="social-media-links UA_ShareModalLinks" style="text-align: left;">
                    <a href="mailto:?&amp;subject=From%20MDPI%3A%20%22Face%20Boundary%20Formulation%20for%20Harmonic%20Models%3A%20Face%20Image%20Resembling&quot;&amp;body=https://www.mdpi.com/3124740%3A%0A%0AFace%20Boundary%20Formulation%20for%20Harmonic%20Models%3A%20Face%20Image%20Resembling

This%20paper%20is%20devoted%20to%20numerical%20algorithms%20based%20on%20harmonic%20transformations%20with%20two%20goals%3A%20%281%29%20face%20boundary%20formulation%20by%20blending%20techniques%20based%20on%20the%20known%20characteristic%20nodes%20and%20%282%29%20some%20challenging%20examples%20of%20face%20resembling.%20The%20formulation%20of%20the%20face%20boundary%20is%20imperative%20for%20face%20recognition%2C%20transformation%2C%20and%20combination.%20Mapping%20between%20the%20source%20and%20target%20face%20boundaries%20with%20constituent%20pixels%20is%20explored%20by%20two%20approaches%3A%20cubic%20spline%20interpolation%20and%20ordinary%20differential%20equation%20%28ODE%29%20using%20Hermite%20interpolation.%20The%20ODE%20approach%20is%20more%20flexible%20and%20suitable%20for%20handling%20different%20boundary%20conditions%2C%20such%20as%20the%20clamped%20and%20simple%20support%20conditions.%20The%20intrinsic%20relations%20between%20the%20cubic%20spline%20and%20ODE%20methods%20are%20explored%20for%20different%20face%20boundaries%2C%20and%20their%20combinations%20are%20developed.%20Face%20combination%20and%20resembling%20are%20performed%20by%20employing%20blending%20curves%20for%20generating%20the%20face%20boundary%2C%20and%20face%20images%20are%20converted%20by%20numerical%20methods%20for%20harmonic%20models%2C%20such%20as%20the%20finite%20difference%20method%20%28FDM%29%2C%20the%20finite%20element%20method%20%28FEM%29%20and%20the%20finite%20volume%20method%20%28FVM%29%20for%20harmonic%20models%2C%20and%20the%20splitting%E2%80%93integrating%20method%20%28SIM%29%20for%20the%20resampling%20of%20constituent%20pixels.%20For%20the%20second%20goal%2C%20the[...]" title="Email">
                        <i class="fa fa-envelope-square" style="font-size: 30px;"></i>
                    </a>

                                        <a href="https://x.com/intent/tweet?text=Face+Boundary+Formulation+for+Harmonic+Models%3A+Face+Image+Resembling&amp;hashtags=mdpijimaging&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F3124740&amp;via=J_Imaging_MDPI" onclick="windowOpen(this.href,600,800); return false" title="Twitter" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
